Load required packages

if (!require("pacman")) install.packages("pacman")
## Loading required package: pacman
pacman::p_load(phyloseq, BiocManager, qiime2R, tidyverse, RColorBrewer, vegan, ggplot2, patchwork)

This step is the only portion of the script that utilizes the Qiime2R plugin. You can change the name of the phyloseq object as needed. You are inputting standard phyloseq requirements but in this case there is no need to convert .qza files as this is handled by the package.

phy = qza_to_phyloseq(features = "barplot_for_paper/filtered-renamed-table.qza", taxonomy = "taxonomy-silva.qza", tree = "rooted-tree.qza", metadata = "barplot_for_paper/04122019_mapping_file_filter_rename.txt",tmp = "/var/folders/67/6dbph7ys1d3240bqc4wgn7380000gp/T/")

Agglomerate to the order and genus level. Transform to relative abundance. Filter out taxa that aren't present at or above 0.001. Convert again to relative abundance so taxa sums to 1.

phy_order_glom = tax_glom(phy, "Order", NArm = F)
phy_genus_glom = tax_glom(phy, "Genus", NArm = F)

ntaxa(phy_order_glom)
## [1] 205
phy_pa_order = transform_sample_counts(phy_order_glom, function(x) x / sum(x))
phy_filter_pa_order = filter_taxa(phy_pa_order, function(x) mean(x) > 1e-3, TRUE)
phy_filter_pa_order = transform_sample_counts(phy_filter_pa_order, function(x) x / sum(x))
ntaxa(phy_filter_pa_order)
## [1] 29
ntaxa(phy_genus_glom)
## [1] 499
phy_pa_genus = transform_sample_counts(phy_genus_glom, function(x) x / sum(x))
phy_filter_pa_genus = filter_taxa(phy_pa_genus, function(x) mean(x) > 1e-3, TRUE)
phy_filter_pa_genus = transform_sample_counts(phy_filter_pa_genus, function(x) x / sum(x))
ntaxa(phy_filter_pa_genus)
## [1] 50

Setting color palette

mycolors <- colorRampPalette(brewer.pal(9, "Set1"))
orderList = unique(tax_table(phy_filter_pa_order)[,"Order"])
orderPalette = mycolors(length(orderList))
names(orderPalette) = orderList
orderPalette["NA"] = "lightgrey"

mycolors <- colorRampPalette(brewer.pal(9, "Set1"))
genusList = unique(tax_table(phy_filter_pa_genus)[,"Genus"])
genusPalette = mycolors(length(genusList))
names(genusPalette) = genusList
genusPalette["NA"] = "grey"

Generate barplot and adjust aesthetics for order level

order_barplot = plot_bar(phy_filter_pa_order, fill = "Order", x = "Basic_Name") + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 30, hjust = 0.8, vjust = 0.8, size = 12), axis.title.x=element_blank(), axis.title.y = element_text(size = 16)) + scale_fill_manual(values = orderPalette, na.value = "grey") + guides(fill=guide_legend(nrow=28)) + ylab("Relative Abundance")
order_barplot

Generate barplot and adjust aesthetics for genus level

genus_barplot = plot_bar(phy_filter_pa_genus, fill = "Genus", x = "Basic_Name") + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 30, hjust = 0.8, vjust = 0.8, size = 12), axis.title.x=element_blank(), axis.title.y = element_text(size = 16)) + scale_fill_manual(values = genusPalette, na.value = "grey") + guides(fill=guide_legend(nrow=40)) + ylab("Relative Abundance")
genus_barplot

Use patchwork to combine plots and organize figure

patchwork_barplot = order_barplot / genus_barplot 
patchwork_barplot + plot_annotation(tag_levels = 'A')

ggsave("barplot_figure.png", width = 14, height = 20)
ggsave("barplot_figure.tiff", width = 14, height = 20, dpi = 300)
